Paris Saint-Germain has officially confirmed that Kylian Mbappe will remain with the club. Mbappe was linked with a move to Real Madrid, as his deal with PSG was to expire in June. However, the 23-year-old has agreed on fresh terms of a three-year current with the Ligue 1 champions. According to Mbappe, Paris is his city and he always wanted to stay. He said: “I’m really happy to continue the adventure here at Paris Saint-Germain. To stay in Paris, my city. “I hope that I will continue to do what I prefer to with you all… and win titles together! Thanks a lot.”